# date data
# insert date data
def calculate_nth_day(date, start_year):
    temp = []
    for i in date:
        start_of_year = datetime(start_year, 1, 1)
        delta = i - start_of_year
        nth_day = delta.days + 1  # Adding 1 to account for the first day
        temp.append(nth_day)
    return temp

# notified datatime is used to genertae day_happen column
not_datetime = df_fire["notified_time"].to_list()
result = calculate_nth_day(not_datetime, YEAR)
print(len(result) == len(not_lu))
#print(result)
df_fire["day_happen"] = result

keelung_district = df_keelung["district"].to_list()
taipei_district = df_taipei["district"].to_list()
taoyuan_district = df_taoyuan["district"].to_list()
newtaipei_district = df_newtaipei["district"].to_list()

def retrieve_cluster(city_district, city_list):
    cluster = []
    for i in city_district:
        for ind, sublist in enumerate(city_list):
            if i in sublist:
                #print(ind, i, sublist)
                cluster.append(1 + ind)
    valid = (len(city_district) == len(cluster))
    if not valid:
        print("failed!")
        raise Exception("Length does not meet!")

    return cluster, valid

keelung_cluster, valid_keelung = retrieve_cluster(keelung_district, keelung_list)
taipei_cluster, valid_taipei = retrieve_cluster(taipei_district, taipei_list)
newtaipei_cluster, valid_newtaipei = retrieve_cluster(newtaipei_district, newtaipei_list)
taoyuan_cluster, valid_taoyuan = retrieve_cluster(taoyuan_district, taoyuan_list)

df_keelung["cluster"] = keelung_cluster
df_taipei["cluster"] = taipei_cluster
df_newtaipei["cluster"] = newtaipei_cluster
df_taoyuan["cluster"] = taoyuan_cluster

# fill out details of the empty streets

def district_rd(city, city_rd):
    # construct road information in city
    rd_info = {}
    for i in range(len(city_rd)):
        district = city_rd["site_id"][i]
        if district not in rd_info.keys():
            rd_info[district] = [city_rd["road"][i]]
        else:
            rd_info[district].append(city_rd["road"][i])
    
    # city
    for j in range(len(city)): # j: each row of data
        if city.loc[j, "street"] == "":
            district_search = city.loc[j, "district"]
            ind = random.randint(0, len(rd_info[district_search]) - 2)
            selected = rd_info[district_search][ind]
            city.loc[j, "street"] = selected
            # pop
            rd_info[district_search].pop(ind)
    return city

keelung = district_rd(df_keelung, keelung_rd)
newtaipei = district_rd(df_newtaipei, newtaipei_rd)
taipei = district_rd(df_taipei, taipei_rd)
taoyuan = district_rd(df_taoyuan, taoyuan_rd)

# append longitude (wgs84aX) and lagitude (wgs84aY) information to each accident

gmaps=googlemaps.Client(key="<API KEY>")
def fetch_coordinate(df_city):
    wgs84aY = [] # wgs84aY
    wgs84aX =[] # wgs84aX
    for i in range(len(df_city)):
        street = df_city["city"][i] + df_city["district"][i] + df_city["street"][i]
        geocode = gmaps.geocode(street)
        long = geocode[0]['geometry']['location']['lng']
        lat = geocode[0]['geometry']['location']['lat']
        wgs84aX.append(long)
        wgs84aY.append(lat)
        print("search:", result[0]["address_components"][0]["long_name"], "actual:", street)
    # append information
    df_city["wgs84aX"] = wgs84aX
    df_city["wgs84aY"] = wgs84aY
    return df_city

df_keelung_n = fetch_coordinate(df_keelung)
df_newtaipei_n = fetch_coordinate(df_newtaipei)
df_taipei_n = fetch_coordinate(df_taipei)

def plot_fire_data(df_city, city_name, city_list):
    '''
    df_city: processes dataframe
    city_name: the city name that one specifies
    df_list: contains fire brigade location in each city
    '''
    
    legend_name = ["brigade 1", "brigade 2", "brigade 3", "brigade 4", "brigade 5", "brigade 6", "brigade 7"]
    color = ["springgreen", "lightgreen", "plum", "lightblue", "cyan", "aliceblue", "lightpink"]
    conversion = {'': "Taoyuan City", "": "Taipei City", "": "New Taipei City", "": "Keelung City"}
    legend_name = ["brigade 1", "brigade 2", "brigade 3", "brigade 4", "brigade 5", "brigade 6", "brigade 7"]
    
    # import shape file
    gdf_district = gp.read_file('./fire_data/map_twdistrict/TOWN_MOI_1120317.shp', encoding="utf-8")
    try:
        df_city_XY = df_city[["wgs84aX", "wgs84aY"]]
    except KeyError:
        print("no such column")
        return
    point_city = [Point(xy) for xy in zip(df_city["wgs84aX"], df_city["wgs84aY"])]
    geopt_city = gp.GeoDataFrame(df_city_XY, geometry=point_city)

    
    gdf_district_city = gdf_district[gdf_district.COUNTYNAME.isin([city_name])]
    ax = gdf_district_city.plot()
    patches = []
    for i in range(len(city_list)):
        gdf_district_city[gdf_district_city.TOWNNAME.isin(city_list[i])].plot(edgecolor=u'gray', color=color[i], ax=ax)
        patches.append(mpatches.Patch(color=color[i], label=legend_name[i]))
        
    minx, miny, maxx, maxy = gdf_district_city.total_bounds
    ax.set_xlim(minx, maxx)
    ax.set_ylim(miny, maxy)
    geopt_city.plot(ax = ax, color = "red", markersize = 5, marker= "o", label="accident_location")

    # Get the handles and labels from the current axes
    handles, labels = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
    # Add the handles and labels from the second legend to the first one
    handles += patches
    labels += legend_name
    
    pos = ax.get_position()
    #ax.set_position([pos.x0, pos.y0, pos.width * 0.9, pos.height])
    ax.legend(loc='center right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.2, 0.8), handles=handles, labels=labels)

    plt.title(f"Accident Location in {YEAR} in {conversion.get(city_name)}")
    #plt.legend()
    plt.show()
